					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 23: 1092-93 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription contains portions of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Pugaḻśūḻnda puṇari</hi> etc., of Kulōttuṅga I. </p>						

						<p>It seems to record some sale of land to the temple by the <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> of Tiruvārūr in Tiruvārūr-kūṟṟam in Gēyamāṇikka-vaḷanāḍu. Other details are lost as the record is built in and incomplete.</p>						

						</summary>
